main event: A record card from Project 10073 detailing a sighting in the Taiwan Straits Area on 24 February 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 15 minutes, The report mentions both aircraft and potential surreptitious activities in the area, Radar analysis attributed the tracks to ground and sea targets, There were no identifiable UFOs observed on radar films, The document is a part of the Project Blue Book investigation.
